Coconut Coleslaw
  --Natasha's Kitchen
  
1/2 medium green cabbage, thinly sliced
1/4 small purple cabbage, very thinly sliced
1/2 c mayo
1/4 c coconut milk (original, unsweetened)
2 tsp granulated sugar
2 tsp apple cider vinegar or lemon juice
1 tsp horseradish cream sauce

In small bowl, whisk together evreything but the cabbage, until creamy and smooth. In medium bowl, combine the cabbages. Add dressing to the cabbage and stir well. Best to let sit in fridge for a while. Stir before serving.

 
